    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Tropical forests deciduous trees, located in areas having a considerable dry season in the low-sun part of the year, huge precipitation totals in the high-sun period, and no freezing temperatures. Examples are in India. </Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
